Lambda Generator Comparison
===========================

Scope
-----

This directory is for one workflow:

1. Produce 10,000-event local NuWro and GiBUU samples.
2. Produce larger GENIE samples on the FNAL grid.
3. Convert every generator output to the same NUISANCE `FlatTree_VARS` ntuple
   shape, then keep the Lambda-topology analysis subset.
4. Run the common matrix/yield analyser and publication plotters.
5. Compare generator models, phase-space regions, expected MicroBooNE event
   yields, and FSI/transport-model differences.

The analysis sample manifest is `analysis/share/config/sample_matrix.tsv`.
Generated analysis ntuples are expected under
`analysis/output/nuisance_flat/<generator>`.

Layout
------

`analysis/bin` contains user-facing commands.

`analysis/lib` contains reusable shell code.

`analysis/libexec/root` contains ROOT/C++ implementation macros, grouped by
task: `matrix`, `yields`, `envelopes`, `coverage`, and `ntuples`.

`analysis/share` contains static cards, flux files, manifests, and cached
GENIE splines.

`analysis/output` contains generated samples, intermediate work, plots, and
tables.

Beam Envelope
-------------

The production-time beam envelope is the generated neutrino-energy range. It is
applied before flattening by the generator wrappers:

```
beam_energy_min_gev=0 beam_energy_max_gev=10 analysis/bin/milestone_10k.sh
```

The same values default the downstream analysis window. Override
`analysis_energy_min_gev` and `analysis_energy_max_gev` only when studying a
subrange of already-produced samples.

Local NuWro/GiBUU Samples
------------------------

Check the local 10,000-event production list:

```
dry_run=1 analysis/bin/milestone_10k.sh
```

Run local production:

```
analysis/bin/milestone_10k.sh
```

`milestone_10k.sh` uses `analysis/share/config/milestone_10k.env`, which sets
`generator_filter=NuWro,GiBUU`. GENIE is intentionally not part of the local
milestone. The local wrappers run the generator, call `nuisflat`, then run the
common analysis-ntuple pass.

GENIE Splines
-------------

`analysis/bin/generate_genie.sh` can create a missing spline locally with
`make_spline=auto`. For grid production, prebuild every configured spline after
sourcing `setup_generators.sh`:

```
mkdir -p analysis/share/splines
for probe in 14 -14; do
  for tune in AR23_20i_00_000 G18_10a_02_11a G18_10b_02_11a G18_10a_02_11b G18_10b_02_11b; do
    gmkspl -p "${probe}" -t 1000180400 -e 10. \
      -o "analysis/share/splines/${probe}_1000180400_CC_v3_6_2_${tune}.xml" \
      --tune "${tune}" --event-generator-list CC
  done
done
```

Regenerate the XML when the probe, target, interaction list, GENIE version,
tune/model setup, or beam-energy envelope changes.

GENIE Grid Samples
------------------

Expand the GENIE rows in the sample manifest into jobsub submissions:

```
dry_run=1 jobs_per_sample=10 events_per_job=200000 \
  analysis/bin/submit_genie_grid_samples.sh
```

Submit them on a uboone GPVM:

```
jobs_per_sample=10 events_per_job=200000 analysis/bin/submit_genie_grid_samples.sh
```

The submitter writes `analysis/output/grid/genie/submissions.tsv`, copies
`production/genie_grid.sh` to `grid_resources_dir`, and uses
`production/submit_genie.sh`. Defaults are:

```
grid_checkout=R-3_06_02
grid_output_base=/pnfs/uboone/persistent/users/$(whoami)/genie_grid
grid_resources_dir=/pnfs/uboone/persistent/users/$(whoami)/grid
```

After grid jobs return, flatten each sample into its manifest target. Example:

```
beam_mode=FHC beam_species=numu \
  analysis/bin/flatten_genie_grid_outputs.sh \
  analysis/output/nuisance_flat/GENIE/GENIE_3.6.2_NuMI_FHC_numu_CC_all_strange_filter_AR23_20i_00_000.flat.root \
  /pnfs/uboone/persistent/users/$(whoami)/genie_grid/GENIE_3.6.2_NuMI_FHC_numu_CC_all_strange_filter_AR23_20i_00_000/*.ghep.root
```

Common Analysis Pass
--------------------

Run the matrix analyser and expected-yield tables after the NuWro/GiBUU local
ntuples and GENIE grid ntuples exist:

```
run_analysis=1 produce_samples=0 analysis/bin/pipeline.sh analysis/share/config/milestone_10k.env
```

The pipeline writes:

```
analysis/output/milestone_10k/matrix/generator_matrix_status.csv
analysis/output/milestone_10k/expected_event_yields/expected_event_yields_by_variation.csv
analysis/output/milestone_10k/expected_event_yields/expected_event_yields_uncertainties.csv
analysis/output/milestone_10k/expected_event_yields/expected_event_yields_generator_envelope.csv
```

To build a common analysis ntuple explicitly from existing NUISANCE flat files:

```
analysis/bin/build_analysis_ntuple.sh output.flat.root input1.flat.root input2.flat.root
```

Add custom per-analysis variables in
`analysis/libexec/root/ntuples/build_analysis_ntuple.cxx` when they are needed.

Plotters
--------

Publication comparison plots from the matrix outputs:

```
analysis/bin/plot_generator_matrix.sh \
  analysis/output/milestone_10k/matrix/generator_matrix_status.csv \
  analysis/output/milestone_10k/matrix \
  analysis/output/milestone_10k/matrix/plots
```

Phase-space plots:

```
analysis/bin/plot_kinematic_coverage.sh \
  analysis/output/milestone_10k/matrix/generator_matrix_status.csv \
  analysis/output/milestone_10k/phase_space \
  "variation beam generator" coverage "enu_q2 q2_w enu_lambda_p w_lambda_p lambda_p_costheta" final_hyperon
```

Generator/configuration envelope plots:

```
analysis/bin/plot_generator_kinematic_envelope.sh \
  analysis/output/milestone_10k/matrix/generator_matrix_status.csv \
  analysis/output/milestone_10k/generator_kinematic_envelope
```

Transport-model comparisons are driven by the `fsi_on` and `fsi_off` rows in
`analysis/share/config/sample_matrix.tsv`; the matrix status CSV and plotters
keep the `fsi_state` in the sample and variation labels.
